My day in the Diamond Capital of the World, Antwerp, was so amazing. Truly a cosy city with pleasant people in it. Did you know every diamond sold anywhere in the world has traveled through Antwerp at least once either to be sold, cut or bought? I think that's so cool.

I went to visit Diamondland Antwerpen to see an actual stonecutter at work. My lovely guide couldn't answer all of my questions though so the 86-year-old stonecutter let me in behind the glass and showed me the workshop from the inside. And how excited do you think I was when he gave me three diamonds for free?? Well they were extremely low quality, way way off the diamond grading scale, but he did tell me to hide them on my way out.

I learned all of these interesting facts about diamonds that I wan't to squeeze in but since you kind of have to be a champion to even make it this far in my caption I simply won't ....
#antwerp #antwerpen #antwerpdiamonds #diamanter #fieldtrip #studiebesök
